---
/**
 * context-engineering 0004 · Figure 2 — "a long-running agent's context, over time".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0004-memory-compression-and-failure-modes.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup id="r2">). Lives as an
 * .astro component for the same reason as Fig1: raw inline SVG with kebab-case
 * attributes is unreliable inside MDX, but is plain HTML inside .astro.
 *
 * The markers this figure references (arwM, arwG) are inlined into its own
 * <defs> — the source page defined them once in a shared <body> <defs> block.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 300"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A long-running agent stores the full transcript externally and assembles a window from system prompt, rolling summary, recent turns, and retrieved facts."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwM"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#b5179e"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >A long-running agent's context, over time</text
        >

        <!-- external transcript -->
        <rect
            x="28"
            y="36"
            width="180"
            height="232"
            rx="9"
            fill="#eef2f7"
            stroke="#1f3a5a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="118" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >Full transcript</text
        >
        <text x="118" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >stored externally (memory)</text
        >
        <rect x="44" y="82" width="148" height="20" rx="4" fill="#dfe7f1"></rect><text
            x="118"
            y="96"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8"
            fill="#6b675f">turn 1 … 12 (old)</text
        >
        <rect x="44" y="106" width="148" height="20" rx="4" fill="#dfe7f1"></rect><text
            x="118"
            y="120"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8"
            fill="#6b675f">turn 13 … 40 (old)</text
        >
        <rect x="44" y="130" width="148" height="20" rx="4" fill="#dfe7f1"></rect><text
            x="118"
            y="144"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8"
            fill="#6b675f">turn 41 … 88 (old)</text
        >
        <rect x="44" y="200" width="148" height="20" rx="4" fill="#cfe0d6"></rect><text
            x="118"
            y="214"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="8"
            fill="#2f5d3a">turn 89 … 92 (recent)</text
        >
        <text x="118" y="256" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-style="italic" fill="#6b675f"
            >nothing is lost here</text
        >

        <!-- summarize arrow -->
        <line
            x1="208"
            y1="120"
            x2="296"
            y2="120"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-dasharray="4 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <text x="252" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >summarize</text
        >
        <line x1="208" y1="210" x2="296" y2="210" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
        <text x="252" y="202" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >verbatim</text
        >

        <!-- the window -->
        <rect
            x="300"
            y="36"
            width="312"
            height="232"
            rx="9"
            fill="#ffffff"
            stroke="#111110"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="456" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >The window (one call · fixed budget)</text
        >
        <rect x="316" y="68" width="280" height="34" rx="5" fill="#efe7f0"></rect><text
            x="456"
            y="89"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#111110">System prompt &amp; instructions</text
        >
        <rect x="316" y="108" width="280" height="46" rx="5" fill="#f1eef2"></rect><text
            x="456"
            y="127"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#b5179e">Rolling summary of everything older</text
        ><text x="456" y="143" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >lossy · regenerated as budget fills</text
        >
        <rect x="316" y="160" width="280" height="46" rx="5" fill="#e9f3ec"></rect><text
            x="456"
            y="179"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#2f5d3a">Last N turns, verbatim</text
        ><text x="456" y="195" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >recent detail kept intact</text
        >
        <rect x="316" y="212" width="280" height="44" rx="5" fill="#eef2f7"></rect><text
            x="456"
            y="231"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="9.5"
            font-weight="700"
            fill="#1f3a5a">Retrieved facts (from KB / memory)</text
        ><text x="456" y="247" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >pulled in for THIS question</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The whole transcript lives in storage; the window is assembled fresh each call. As the
        budget fills, <b>old turns get summarized</b> while <b
            >recent turns and decisions stay verbatim</b
        > — this is Lesson 4 M1 in action: store it all, retrieve on demand.<sup
            ><a href="#s2" id="r2">2</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
